♪ Giddy up ♪♪ Oom-poppa, oom-poppa ♪

13:57.967 --> 13:59.795
♪ Mow, mow ♪♪ Giddy up ♪

13:59.882 --> 14:03.451
♪ Oom-poppa, oom-poppa,
mow, mow ♪

14:03.538 --> 14:06.193
♪ Hi-ho, Silver ♪

14:06.280 --> 14:09.326
♪ Away ♪

14:09.413 --> 14:10.719
[phone rings]

14:10.806 --> 14:11.938
♪ Tonight I'm gonna... ♪

14:12.025 --> 14:14.723
Hey, sweetie, what's up?

14:14.810 --> 14:16.812
Aw.

14:24.472 --> 14:26.169
B-9.

14:27.214 --> 14:29.085
B-9.

14:29.172 --> 14:31.261
What did he say?

14:31.348 --> 14:34.351
B-9!

14:34.438 --> 14:35.918
Right there.

14:36.005 --> 14:36.788
You've got bingo. Again.

14:36.876 --> 14:39.008
Oh.

14:39.095 --> 14:41.445
Uh, bingo!

14:41.532 --> 14:43.012
How the hell does
she keep winning?

14:43.099 --> 14:45.667
She doesn't even
know where she is.

14:47.190 --> 14:48.539
It's those lucky charms.

14:48.626 --> 14:49.845
Think she'd notice
if I took her troll?

14:49.932 --> 14:51.238
Which one-- the one
on the table

14:51.325 --> 14:52.282
or the one sitting
across from her?

14:52.369 --> 14:53.283
The one with the pink hair.

14:53.370 --> 14:54.894
Again, same question.

14:57.853 --> 14:58.636
How about we head out soon?

14:58.723 --> 15:00.377
We can't leave now.

15:00.464 --> 15:02.205
They save the good prizes
till the end.

15:02.292 --> 15:04.555
I got my eye on that foot spa.

15:04.642 --> 15:05.817
Okay, well,
what if I come back later

15:05.905 --> 15:08.124
and just pick you up?

15:08.211 --> 15:09.256
Is it really that awful

15:09.343 --> 15:10.953
spending time with your mother?

15:11.040 --> 15:14.435
There is no right answer
to that question.

15:14.522 --> 15:15.610
Well, now my dabber's dry.

15:15.697 --> 15:17.264
Go and get me a new one.

15:17.351 --> 15:19.266
Oh, and don't buy anything
from Sister Anne.

15:19.353 --> 15:22.225
She hasn't sold a winning
card since Vatican Two.Oh.

15:24.358 --> 15:26.012
Hey, man.

15:26.099 --> 15:27.187
Why are you putting
us through this?

15:27.274 --> 15:29.102
Well, what am I
supposed to do?

15:29.189 --> 15:31.060
Give your mom back her
car and take my money.

15:31.147 --> 15:32.757
Look, it's never
gonna happen, Carl.

15:32.844 --> 15:34.716
Why not?'Cause I've got my pride.

15:34.803 --> 15:36.413
Wha..? Man, you're
in a church basement

15:36.500 --> 15:38.285
trying to beat out some old
biddies for a toaster oven.

15:38.372 --> 15:40.504
I think your pride's
pretty much shot!

15:40.591 --> 15:42.811
They're starting a new game.
Are we done here?

15:42.898 --> 15:44.508
No, we are not.
Not until you explain to me

15:44.595 --> 15:46.380
why in the hell you won't
let me loan you money.

15:46.467 --> 15:47.598
Because that's not the way our
relationship's supposed to work.

15:47.685 --> 15:49.078
I'm supposed
to take care of you.

15:49.165 --> 15:50.384
Come on, man.
We-we help each other.

15:50.471 --> 15:51.820
We're brothers.

15:51.907 --> 15:53.430
Yeah, but I'm the big brother.
I help you.

15:53.517 --> 15:55.476
You break up, I console you.

15:55.563 --> 15:57.304
You mouth off at a bar,
I take the punch.

15:57.391 --> 15:59.001
They threaten to throw you out
of the police softball league,

15:59.088 --> 16:00.742
I say, "If he goes, I go."

16:00.829 --> 16:03.397
Even though you were dressed
like an idiot.

16:03.484 --> 16:05.747
Man, I just got back from
rollerblading, all right?

16:05.834 --> 16:07.662
And didn't have time to
change out of my Lululemons.Okay.

16:07.749 --> 16:10.186
Listen.

16:10.273 --> 16:12.101
I know you look out
for me, right?

16:12.188 --> 16:13.537
But why can't I look out for you
every once in a while, huh?

16:13.624 --> 16:15.017
Help my big brother.Look, Carl.

16:15.104 --> 16:16.192
Really appreciate it.
I just can't.

16:16.279 --> 16:17.367
What the hell's
taking so long?

16:17.454 --> 16:18.455
Where's my dabber?

16:18.542 --> 16:20.109
Sorry, I was talking to Carl.

16:20.196 --> 16:21.545
Oh, didn't mean
to interrupt.

16:21.632 --> 16:23.156
You said you were
gonna do something,

16:23.243 --> 16:24.244
I just thought you might
actually do it.

16:24.331 --> 16:26.420
I am doing it!
It's fine.

16:26.507 --> 16:27.421
Don't trouble yourself.

16:27.508 --> 16:29.249
You got what you want.

16:29.336 --> 16:32.469
Sister Bernadette,
give me a red dabber.

16:32.556 --> 16:36.343
The color of the blood
we bleed for our children.

16:38.736 --> 16:40.564
I'm gonna want
to pay you interest.

16:40.651 --> 16:42.479
I wouldn't have it
any other way.

16:42.566 --> 16:44.699
MAN: O-69.

16:44.786 --> 16:45.569
Bingo!

16:45.656 --> 16:47.093
I won! I won!

16:47.180 --> 16:48.964
In your face, Gladys.

16:49.051 --> 16:51.749
Eh, where's your
lucky troll now?

17:01.716 --> 17:03.413
Man, when I gave you that money,

17:03.500 --> 17:04.675
I thought you'd go put
a down payment on a new car.

17:04.762 --> 17:07.200
Hey, a new engine
is a new car.

17:07.287 --> 17:09.811
Like putting a fresh
liver into an old wino.

17:09.898 --> 17:11.856
What about the hole
in the floor,

17:11.943 --> 17:14.163
uh, the windows
that don't roll up

17:14.250 --> 17:15.730
and the crappy
electrical system?

17:15.817 --> 17:18.602
Where's all this negativity
coming from?

17:20.430 --> 17:22.302
This should be a day
of celebration like Easter.

17:22.389 --> 17:25.392
In three days,
the Galant has risen.

17:25.479 --> 17:27.263
I don't get you at all.

17:27.350 --> 17:29.048
Well, what's to get?
I'm a loyal guy.

17:29.135 --> 17:30.832
And if something's been
good to me, I stick with it.

17:30.919 --> 17:33.313
Even if it has no value,
and people laugh at it.

17:33.400 --> 17:35.793
Kind of explains why
you're my best friend.

17:35.880 --> 17:37.012
Was that a compliment?

17:37.099 --> 17:40.407
It's as good
as you're gonna get.

17:40.494 --> 17:41.712
All right, if you're
happy, I'm happy.

17:41.799 --> 17:43.671
Thanks, pal. All right.

17:43.758 --> 17:45.977
What do you say we crank up some
tunes and get this engine in?

17:46.065 --> 17:47.283
All right, sounds good.Let's do it.

17:47.370 --> 17:49.198
♪ I'm singing Elvira... ♪

17:49.285 --> 17:50.982
Oh, no!

17:51.070 --> 17:52.810
Oh, yes. I finally got the tape
out of the Impala.

17:52.897 --> 17:55.596
Come on, sing it with me.

